snippet.textDisplay:
Came back to this song after a long time! Still feels so fresh and ahead of its time.
Hats off clinton cerejo, your thinking made this work. Kudos to manoj yadav, such deeply rooted words and a powerful message!
Also what a kickass bass, chorus vocals, drums and uff that guitar solo!
Last but not the least, bow down to kailash kher. Nobody could have pulled off this except him. That last hark of 'kalapi kalapi' is so transcending.
God give peace to the ones who love this and some musical sense to the ones who are not fond of such a masterpiece.
Truly jamaican reggae with indian flavour
Bob marley would have loved this if he was there to listen to this!
